   "source": [
    "if we consider that pos is an array with a position for each piece and turn keeps track of whose turn it is(0 for white and 1 for black) we can represent the states as such:\n",
    "initial state: \n",
    "S(pos, turn)\n",
    "\n",
    "state awww\n",
    "\n",
    "initial state: S(0,0)\n",
    "state representation: S(w1,w2), w1 = 0..c1, w2 = 0..c2\n",
    "operators: \n",
    "    Name        Preconditions           effects             cost\n",
    "    Fill1       S(_,w2)                 S(c1,w2)            1\n",
    "    Fill2       S(w1,_)                 S(w1,c2)            1\n",
    "    Empty1      S(_,w2)                 S(0,w2)             1\n",
    "    Empty2      S(w1,_)                 S(w1,_)             1\n",
    "    Pour1Fill2  S(w1,w2), w1+w1 > c2    S(w1-(c2-w2),c2)    1\n",
    "    Pour1Empty  S(w1,w2), w1+w2 <= c2   S(0,w2+w1)          1\n",
    "    Pour2Fill1  S(w1,w2), w1+w2 > c1    S(c1,w2-(c1-w1))    1\n",
    "    Pour1Empty  S(w1,w2), w1+w2 <= c1   S(w1+w2,0)          1\n",
    "final state: S(n,_)"
   ]
